likelihood ratio statistic has a conditional null limit distribution \$G{\textbackslash}neq{\textbackslash}chi{\textasciicircum}2\_1\$ determined by the joint limit theorem. We show through this route that no advantage is gained by extending the single distribution \$F\_1\$ to the nonparametric composite mixture generated by the same tail-equivalence class.},
